dataIdInfo.idPurp: A point file of various place locations (city, town, village, neighborhood, tribal community, and unincorporated place) in New York State.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Centroid point locations for cities, towns, villages, tribal communities, neighborhoods, and unincorporated places in New York State. Places that cross county boundaries have only one point location and one county assigned.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: NYS Office of Information Technology Services GIS Program Office (GPO)

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Name of the city, town, village, neighborhood, tribal community, or unincorporated place.
Type of place location. Values are: Incorporated City Incorporated Town Incorporated Village Neighborhood Tribal Community Unincorporated Place

Designates which location should be returned when geocoding and there is a duplicate Name. The order is as follows:
1 – City 2 – Village 3 – Town 4 – Unincorporated Place 5 – Neighborhood
Indian Territories do not have a rank because there aren’t any duplicate names.
If [PLACETYPE] = 'Neighborhood' this field is populated with the name of the city in which the neighborhood is located.
The name of the county in which the point location is placed. In cases where the place falls in more than one county, only ONE point location and ONE county is assigned.
Name of the State the point location is located in. All values are "New York State". This field is used for geocoding purposes.
The date the point location and/or attribute data was last modified DD/MM/YYYY.
